# Molecular Visualization Tool

##  Project Statement
Molecular structure is critical to chemistry, biology, materials science, etc., but using only static pictures or textbook diagrams to show the molecules do not demonstrate their actual three-dimensional reality and complexity to the user.



The objective of our project is to create an **Interactive 3D Molecular Visualisation** system so users can view and interact with atoms, bonds, and molecular geometries in a two-dimensional and three-dimensional space, helping users to understand the nature of the molecular system while engaging with it at the same time.

##  Objectives
- To produce a 3-D method of visualizing molecular structure through the use of an interactive (real-time) interface
- To represent both the atomic and bonding aspect of shapes via graphical representations
- To allow for the viewing of 3D manipulation through rotating, zooming in/out and panning around 3D shapes
- To produce an easy-to-use interface for both students as well as researchers
- To enhance a learning experience with real-time visualization.

##  Features
- Model of Structure of Molecules in three dimensions  
- Use of colours to differentiate types of molecules  
- Rotation, Zoom and Pan functions available  
- Capability to load molecular data such as .pdb or .xyz  
- Scalable and modular design structure.

 ##  Problem It Solves
  The reason many students have difficulty visualizing molecules' three-dimensional shapes is that they need to understand how molecules behave chemically and interact with each other. This tool provides the means to bridge the gap between abstract molecular data and visual representations through an interactive approach to visualizing molecules.

 ##  Future Scope
- Integration with real-time simulation (e.g., molecular dynamics)  
- AR/VR-based molecular exploration  
- Database integration for large molecule libraries  
- AI-based structure prediction visualization  
